# Router Core

## Treat `src/routing.ts` as high-risk

- Changes to `location`, `matches`, `params`, `navigate`, `beforeLeave`, or integration flow usually affect the whole library.
- Do not change public location semantics casually; validate whether a change is a real model shift or only a rename.
- Preserve the distinction between browser-initiated and library-initiated navigation unless you are intentionally redesigning it.

## Navigation Work

- Check `beforeLeave`, retry behavior, redirects, query-only navigations, and integration synchronization together.
- Be explicit about `flush()` usage. If it remains, justify why the synchronous visibility is required.
- When refactoring router internals, call out whether the result is truly simpler or only repackaged.

## Validation

- Prefer `test/router.spec.ts` for router-core behavior changes.
- If changing integration behavior, check `test/integration.spec.ts` too.
